The enemy freezes in place, and after a brief delay, teleports directly behind the nearest player. After teleporting, the enemy cannot move or attack for 1 second.

The enemy charges up power. After a delay, Speed II, and Resistance II are applied to the 3 closest hostile mobs for 15 seconds. Additionally, the mobs attacks will do 50% additional damage as true damage for the duration, as well as inflict any traits inherited from the Augmenter. The augmenter is immobilized (if ground based) while charging. Non-hit traits the Augmenter has will be cast at the positions of all buffed mobs. If the Augmenter is the only mob within radius, it buffs itself instead.
The mob charges up and then launches a rapid flurry of projectiles at the nearest player. 8 projectiles are fired over 4 seconds. The mob moves slower while firing.
The enemy roars. After a brief delay, they charge in a straight line in the direction they are facing. Players in the charge path are run over, taking damage.
The enemy sounds a horn and then applies all its non-hit traits to the 3 nearest enemies once.

The enemy shouts, and after a brief delay, creates an exact copy of itself. These copies replicate held items and armor. Copies are spawned with 50% the remaining health of the mob and vanish after existing for 18 seconds. When duplicates are killed (not vanished), they deal 4 damage to all entities (including players) within 2 blocks.
Zombies, Husks, Drowned, Skeletons, Strays, Wither Skeletons, Pillagers, Vindicators, Piglins, Creepers, Spiders, Cave Spiders

The enemy creates an invulnerable spectre that chases players, damaging them if close. The Spectre lasts 10 seconds and briefly slows down after hitting a player. The Spectre has an attack radius of 2 blocks and can only attack every second.

The enemy charges up. After a long channel, they heal the closest 3 enemies within 10 blocks for 30% of their max health. The healer is immobilized (if ground based) while charging. Non-hit traits the Healer has will be cast at the positions of all healed mobs. If the Healer is the only mob within radius, it heals itself instead.

The enemy winds up and shoots a hook at a player. If the hook connects, the player takes damage, and is slowly dragged towards the mob over the next 5 seconds. While being dragged, the player moves 50% slower. The dragging effect ends after those 5 seconds, or if the hookshot mob attacks the player.

The enemy becomes immobile (if ground based) and channels a laser at the nearest player. At the end of the channel, the laser casts an explosion at the end of it, dealing explosive damage and knocking enemies back. The laser can be blocked by moving out of line of sight of an enemy, exploding instead at the obstruction. The explosion breaks blocks.

The mob channels and after a second, creates three masses that rotate around it. These masses deal damage based on the mob's attack stat if they pass through a player. These orbs remain for 8 seconds.

The enemy prepares. After it prepares, within the next 3 seconds, it will fire a fast ranged attack at the player's position. The attack will knock the enemy back a slight distance, and the enemy gains Speed I (0:04) to catch back up to the target.

The enemy channels for a very brief duration and then summons mini-lightning strikes around nearby players or itself. The amount of lightning summoned is dependent on the difficulty. The lightning detonates very shortly after, damaging players within the range.
The enemy creates a noise and then summons 1 to 3 mobs based on the offhand spawn egg it is holding.
The enemy prepares. After it prepares, within the next 3 seconds, it will quickly slash in a cone in front of it, dealing damage. The enemy will also dash forwards a slight distance.
The enemy charges up. After a delay, it throws a minimum of 3 projectiles in a cone towards the player.
When the enemy dies, all enemies within 16 blocks gain +10% Melee Attack Damage, and are healed for 4 health. This buff can stack up to +100% Attack Damage.

When the enemy dies, all enemies within 16 blocks gain +30% Cooldown Reduction, and are healed for 4 health. This buff can stack up to +300% Cooldown Reduction. If an enemy has no active ability, it gains a Relentless stack (movement speed) instead.
When the enemy dies, nearby mobs gain +5% Speed and are healed for 4 health. This buff can stack up to +50% Speed.

When the enemy dies, nearby mobs gain 1 Absorption Shielding and are healed for 4 health. Each time an entity receives an Absorption Shielding from Sacrificial Blood, the Shielding they receive is +1 additional Absorption Shielding.

When the enemy dies, they drop 2-3 copies of their offhand egg as Corpse Crawler eggs. After 3 seconds, the eggs hatch into the corresponding mob (with a baby zombie variant if no mob was specified). Eggs have 8 health, and can be destroyed by any attacks, preventing the spawn.

When the enemy dies, they drop their weapon and reincarnate as a soul nearby. The soul attempts to reclaim its weapon by moving towards it. If it is successful, the soul will respawn as the original entity.
When the enemy dies, they drop a block of ignited TNT where they die. The TNT has a fuse of 4 seconds.
On death, the enemy drops an environmental hazard based on its traits. The hazards can create new blocks or be temporary zones that clear after a short time.

When the enemy dies, they leave behind a remnant of the spawn egg they were carrying. This remnant will spawn the mob inside it after 1.5 seconds. (A Spectre enemy is spawned if no enemy is specified).

giz.advancements.root.2: View the progress of your journey
giz.functions.boss.1.start_check.1: All sorcerers must be prepared to challenge what lies ahead.
giz.functions.boss.1.start_check.2: Entering will link your lives. Are you prepared?
giz.functions.boss.4.start_check.1: As you attempt to pass the gate, a otherworldly heat nearly burns you, you'll need to find some sort of protection.
giz.functions.dialogue.calaeyth.1.12: I do hope my notes can help you, in whatever way they can.
giz.functions.dialogue.calaeyth.1.2: Ah, you must be an adventurer! A rare occasion indeed. Welcome to my gardens!
giz.functions.dialogue.calaeyth.1.6: If you find any rare looking plants, bring them to the room behind me, I'll be willing to share my studies about them!
giz.functions.dialogue.calaeyth.1.8: Ah, its you. I must thank you, for taking the time to find those plants.
giz.functions.dialogue.calaeyth.2.2: If you truly are an adventurer, and I have no doubt about it, would you be willing to help out?
giz.functions.dialogue.calaeyth.3.2: If you spot any rare plants outside of this Sanctuary, could you bring them to the room behind me?
giz.functions.dialogue.calaeyth.4.2: I have little for reward, but I'll share my knowledge on the plants!
giz.functions.dialogue.cosmic.1.2: Hello? Who's there? Are you here about my shop?
giz.functions.dialogue.cosmic.2.2: Unfortunately, I don't really work there anymore... not since Warpshard installed those machines.
giz.functions.dialogue.cosmic.3.2: Ever since one of those... creatures found their way into Renelya, Warpshard forced us all to stay in our apartments. For our safety they said.
giz.functions.dialogue.cosmic.4.2: I wish I could get back to serving customers myself, but... seems like I won't have that chance again.
giz.functions.dialogue.gilbert.1.6: Oh piss off. What do you want from me? Trying to start something?
giz.functions.dialogue.gilbert.2.2: Ahh, I know... You're another one of those entitled bastards from Warpshard, aren't you?
giz.functions.dialogue.gilbert.3.2: Come to take even more from us? Whatever, just leave me alone. I can't stand the lot of ya.
giz.functions.dialogue.lyra.2.2: Suppose you'll be on your journey soon? Well, I wish you luck. It's pretty bad out there... although I'm sure Madeline would be willing to help!
giz.functions.dialogue.madeline.1.2.2: We finally found you... Allow me to introduce myself, I'm Madeline.
giz.functions.dialogue.madeline.1.3.2: Once you're through to the other side, come talk with us... are you ready? Sorcerer?
giz.functions.dialogue.madeline.2.1.12: Illmere settled in this place long ago, before being found by Renelya.
giz.functions.dialogue.madeline.2.1.6: Meet with me near the Warpshard Sanctuary, I'll be willing to help you with your quest!
giz.functions.dialogue.madeline.2.1.8: Oh, welcome back Sorcerer. What brings you back here?
giz.functions.dialogue.madeline.2.2.2: We have summoned you to this world, in need of your aid.
giz.functions.dialogue.madeline.2.3.2: This world is burning, and is beyond repair. So I ask we proceed with haste.
giz.functions.dialogue.madeline.2.4.2: There is an Altar, which may very well be the only escape from this world. We ask you to help us power it.
giz.functions.dialogue.madeline.2.5.2: I wish you luck, this world won't have mercy on you. Oh, another matter, talk with me near the Warpshard Sanctuary, I'll be willing to help you on your quest.
giz.functions.dialogue.madeline.2.6.2: If you wish, I could tell you a bit about us. We are... hiding, from Warpshard. Long ago we made a grave mistake, one which they didn't forgive... and well, here are we now.
giz.functions.dialogue.madeline.2.7.2: I remember the stories my mother told me, about the travels from a far away land...
giz.functions.dialogue.madeline.2.8.2: But it makes me think, if they didn't make this place... what lived down here before they arrived?
giz.functions.dialogue.madeline.3.1.10: Thank you Sorcerer, speak with Vetra in Renelya, when you're ready.
giz.functions.dialogue.madeline.3.1.12: Ah, you've returned, have you changed your mind?
giz.functions.dialogue.madeline.3.1.18: Good to see you, I suppose you've met Vetra?
giz.functions.dialogue.madeline.3.1.2: Ah, good to see you, I hope your quest has been going well.
giz.functions.dialogue.madeline.3.1.22: Ahh, the gemstones! Thank you, for helping me retrieve them.
giz.functions.dialogue.madeline.3.1.26: Meet me at the Altar. The magic from the vessels should be enough to awaken these gemstones.
giz.functions.dialogue.madeline.3.1.28: Sorcerer, if you ever enter the ruins of Illmere, please be careful. I can't even imagine what lives there now...
giz.functions.dialogue.madeline.3.1.6: Oh, I was hoping you would come, glad to see you here, Sorcerer.
giz.functions.dialogue.madeline.3.2.2: Anyway, I have a favor to ask... there is a special gemstone in the Renelya Vault, it can be used to channel cosmic energy.
giz.functions.dialogue.madeline.3.3.2: But the vault seems to be locked by a Shimmerstone key. Fortunately, I know someone in Renelya who could help us out!
giz.functions.dialogue.madeline.3.4.2: If you help out, I'll be willing to create some cosmic infused equipment for you.
giz.functions.dialogue.madeline.3.5.2: Thank you Sorcerer, speak with Vetra in Renelya when you're ready.
giz.functions.dialogue.madeline.3.6.2: Very well then, talk with me if you ever change your mind.
giz.functions.dialogue.madeline.3.7.2: This task is certainly risky, but, you can trust her. She's been there for me, and Illmere for many years. And she still trusts us, despite what happened...
giz.functions.dialogue.madeline.3.8.2: Hmm... it seems the energy in them has become dormant... but, I might be able to awake it again.
giz.functions.dialogue.madeline.4.1.10: Ah Sorcerer, glad to see you well. Found any more vessels?
giz.functions.dialogue.madeline.4.1.14: Ah, Sorcerer, I've attempted to awaken the Gemstones, but, I think we need more vessels to do so.
giz.functions.dialogue.madeline.4.1.18: Oh, Sorcerer! Just in time! I've just awakened the gemstones.
giz.functions.dialogue.madeline.4.1.2: Glad to see you well. If you find any vessels for this altar, could you bring them to me?
giz.functions.dialogue.madeline.4.1.22: After Illmere fell, the survivors needed a leader... I was given that role.
giz.functions.dialogue.madeline.4.1.26: Ah there you are, glad to see you well. Found any more vessels?
giz.functions.dialogue.madeline.4.1.30: Thank you for helping us, Sorcerer.
giz.functions.dialogue.madeline.4.2.2: Being here... it takes me back. To my childhood here in Illmere... before it fell.
giz.functions.dialogue.madeline.4.3.2: Illmere was a wonderful place, focused on studying the magic contained within the vast cosmos.
giz.functions.dialogue.madeline.4.4.2: But... that eventually became Illmere's end on that fateful day.
giz.functions.dialogue.madeline.4.5.2: Their glow is beautiful... alright! Let's see what I can make for you. As my thanks.
giz.functions.dialogue.madeline.4.6.2: When you're ready, I'll infuse a single weapon of your choice with the gemstone's energy.

giz.functions.dialogue.madeline.4.7.2: Unfortunately I... couldn't protect all of them...
giz.functions.dialogue.madeline.4.8.2: But even if Illmere is lost, isn't everyone else still worth fighting for?
giz.functions.dialogue.madeline.bow.2: Very well then, I hope this can help on your quest!
giz.functions.dialogue.restul.1.10: Oh, it's you. Have you found her yet?
giz.functions.dialogue.restul.1.2: Oh, hello there... You're a new face around here. I'm Restul.
giz.functions.dialogue.restul.1.6: Anne... please forgive me. I should have never left you alone... I'm sorry...
giz.functions.dialogue.restul.2.2: I'm afraid you've caught me at a bad time... unless... you would be kind enough to help me?
giz.functions.dialogue.restul.3.2: My friend, Anne, has gone missing... I've searched all of Warpshard and Renelya for her... but, nothing.
giz.functions.dialogue.restul.4.2: I fear that she's outside the Sanctuary somewhere. Would you please help search for her? Before... something else finds her first...
giz.functions.dialogue.restul.5.2: Oh, I didn't see you there... have you found her yet?
giz.functions.dialogue.restul.6.2: Is this... oh... Anne... w-well. Thank you for, f-for finding this for me... here, take this, for your kindness.
giz.functions.dialogue.roger.1.2: Greetings, Sorcerer. Welcome to our hideout... well, what remains of it at least.
giz.functions.dialogue.roger.1.6: Ah I see you took me up on my offer, alright, what do you need?
giz.functions.dialogue.roger.2.2: We barely survived when those creatures got in, so I would recommend caution ahead.
giz.functions.dialogue.roger.3.2: I have prepared this chest for you, its not much, but it should help... and if you're willing to trade, come talk with me again.
giz.functions.dialogue.vetra.1.10: Oh, I see you found a Shimmerstone Shard!
giz.functions.dialogue.vetra.1.14: Oh, hello, you're right on time! I just finished the key. Here you go!
giz.functions.dialogue.vetra.1.18: I wish you luck on your journey!
giz.functions.dialogue.vetra.1.2: Oh, you must be the Sorcerer? A pleasure to meet you. Vetra's the name.
giz.functions.dialogue.vetra.1.6: Oh, hello. I apologize for any inconvenience but I'm currently quite busy.
giz.functions.dialogue.vetra.1.8: Somewhere in the Warpshard Cliffs, there should be a way down into the mines, in there you'll be able to find the Shimmerstone Shard we need.
giz.functions.dialogue.vetra.2.2: Madeline has told me all about you. Now then, I suppose you're here to get into that vault?
giz.functions.dialogue.vetra.3.2: Seems quite risky, but it should be possible. If I'm correct, all we'll need is a Shimmerstone Shard and some scraps of metal to create the key.
giz.functions.dialogue.vetra.4.2: I got the metal all sorted, but that shard... I'll need your help to get that.
giz.functions.dialogue.vetra.5.2: Most of the shimmerstone is with Warpshard, but we can't exactly go asking them. But, their old mine might have some... hmm...
giz.functions.dialogue.vetra.7.2: I'll begin working on this key, give me some time and it'll be all ready.
giz.functions.dialogue.vetra.8.2: I hope you and Madeline can find what you're looking for in there.
